Note: ================================================================
Note: Verilog Parser
Note: ================================================================
Note: Parses Verilog HDL source code into Abstract Syntax Tree (AST).
Note: Comprehensive coverage of Verilog-2001/2005 constructs.
Note: ================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/verilog/verilog_lexer.runa" as VerilogLexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore

Note: ================================================================
Note: AST Node Type Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant NODE_SOURCE_FILE as Integer is 1
Constant NODE_MODULE as Integer is 2
Constant NODE_PORT_DECLARATION as Integer is 3
Constant NODE_NET_DECLARATION as Integer is 4
Constant NODE_REG_DECLARATION as Integer is 5
Constant NODE_INTEGER_DECLARATION as Integer is 6
Constant NODE_PARAMETER as Integer is 7
Constant NODE_ALWAYS_BLOCK as Integer is 8
Constant NODE_INITIAL_BLOCK as Integer is 9
Constant NODE_ASSIGN as Integer is 10
Constant NODE_MODULE_INSTANTIATION as Integer is 11
Constant NODE_BLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT as Integer is 12
Constant NODE_NONBLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT as Integer is 13
Constant NODE_IF_STATEMENT as Integer is 14
Constant NODE_CASE_STATEMENT as Integer is 15
Constant NODE_FOR_LOOP as Integer is 16
Constant NODE_WHILE_LOOP as Integer is 17
Constant NODE_BEGIN_END_BLOCK as Integer is 18
Constant NODE_FUNCTION_DECLARATION as Integer is 19
Constant NODE_TASK_DECLARATION as Integer is 20
Constant NODE_GENERATE_BLOCK as Integer is 21
Constant NODE_SENSITIVITY_LIST as Integer is 22
Constant NODE_EXPRESSION as Integer is 23
Constant NODE_BINARY_OP as Integer is 24
Constant NODE_UNARY_OP as Integer is 25
Constant NODE_CONDITIONAL_EXPR as Integer is 26
Constant NODE_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 27
Constant NODE_NUMBER as Integer is 28
Constant NODE_BIT_SELECT as Integer is 29
Constant NODE_PART_SELECT as Integer is 30
Constant NODE_CONCATENATION as Integer is 31
Constant NODE_SYSTEM_TASK_CALL as Integer is 32
Constant NODE_STRING_LITERAL as Integer is 33
Constant NODE_GENVAR_DECLARATION as Integer is 34
Constant NODE_DIRECTIVE as Integer is 35

Note: ================================================================
Note: Parser State
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
The Verilog parser maintains a flat three-slot state: the token
list (produced by the lexer), the current index (advanced
monotonically through parsing), and an error list for parse
failures. Verilog's grammar is rich (modules, ports, declarations,
always-blocks, generate blocks) but the parser stays single-pass;
no lookahead beyond the immediate token is required because the
grammar is largely LR(1).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three i64-sized fields, 24 bytes total at offsets 0, 8, 16. The
tokens field is a pointer to a List of token records (each token
is itself a record produced by VerilogLexer with type @0, string
or value @8, line @24, column @32). Current is a plain integer
index into that list; errors is a List of error records each
holding message, line, column. No mutable per-token state - all
parser state is the index.
@End Implementation
Type called "VerilogParser":
    tokens as Integer  Note: Pointer to list of tokens
    current as Integer  Note: Current token index
    errors as Integer  Note: Pointer to list of parse errors
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Parser Initialization
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Constructs a VerilogParser record from a pre-tokenised token list.
The current-index starts at 0 and a fresh empty errors_list is
allocated so the caller does not have to thread error state.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes (three i64 slots). Writes tokens_list @0,
current_index = 0 @8, and a freshly-allocated empty List @16.
Returns the parser_ptr.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_parser" that takes tokens_list as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Create and initialize a Verilog parser state.
    @End Reasoning

    Let parser_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 0, tokens_list
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 8, 0  Note: current index

    Let errors_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 16, errors_list

    Return parser_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Token Navigation
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Returns the full token pointer at the current parser position
without advancing. Used when a parsing helper needs more than just
the token type (e.g. to read an identifier's string payload via
read_string).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the tokens_list pointer @0 and current_index @8 from the
parser state. Calls List.get_from_list to index into the token
array; returns the token pointer (or 0 if index is past the end).
@End Implementation
Process called "peek" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Get current token without advancing.
    @End Reasoning

    Let tokens_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 0
    Let current_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 8

    Return proc list_get from ListCore with tokens_list, current_index
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shortcut to read the token TYPE at the current position. Most
dispatch decisions in the parser only need the type byte, not the
full token record - returning the type directly saves the caller a
read.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads token_ptr via peek. If 0 (past EOF), returns TOKEN_EOF from
the lexer module so callers can match against a sentinel without
special-casing null. Otherwise reads the integer at offset 0 of the
token record (the token-type field).
@End Implementation
Process called "peek_type" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Get current token type without advancing.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_ptr be proc peek with parser_ptr

    If token_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return TOKEN_EOF from VerilogLexer
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-step consume: returns the current token pointer and bumps
the current index by one. The returned pointer is the token the
caller wanted to capture before moving past it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads token_ptr via peek (current token pointer, may be 0 at EOF).
Reads current_index @8 and writes back current_index + 1. Returns
token_ptr. No bounds check here; peek will return 0 past EOF and
the caller's subsequent peek_type will return TOKEN_EOF.
@End Implementation
Process called "advance" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Move to next token and return current token.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_ptr be proc peek with parser_ptr

    Let current_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 8, current_index plus 1

    Return token_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Mandatory consume: if the current token type matches the expected
type, consumes and returns it; otherwise emits an "Unexpected
token" error and returns 0 without advancing. Unlike match(),
treats a mismatch as a parse error rather than a normal branch.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads token_type via peek_type. If equal to expected_type, returns
proc advance (which also returns the just-consumed token pointer).
Otherwise calls add_parse_error with message "Unexpected token" and
returns 0 - the caller may continue parsing under error-recovery
semantics.
@End Implementation
Process called "expect" that takes parser_ptr as Integer, expected_type as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Expect a specific token type and consume it, or report error.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    If token_type is equal to expected_type:
        Return proc advance with parser_ptr
    Otherwise:
        proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Unexpected token"
        Return 0
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Conditional consume: peek at the current token type; if it matches
the expected type, advance and return 1. Otherwise leave the parser
position unchanged and return 0. Used when the next token is
optional (lookahead-style decisions).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads current_type via peek_type. If current_type == token_type,
calls advance (discarding the returned token) and returns 1.
Otherwise returns 0 with no side effects on parser state.
@End Implementation
Process called "match" that takes parser_ptr as Integer, token_type as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Check if current token matches type and consume if true.
    @End Reasoning

    Let current_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    If current_type is equal to token_type:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Main Parsing Entry Point
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Top-level entry point: parses an entire Verilog source file as a
list of modules (and any compiler directives). Builds a
NODE_SOURCE_FILE root node whose children are the modules and
directives in source order. Unknown top-level tokens generate
error recovery by skipping one token.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 16 bytes for NODE_SOURCE_FILE. Writes type @0. Creates an
empty modules_list and writes @8. Loop until EOF:
  - TOKEN_MODULE -> parse_module, append to modules_list
  - TOKEN_DIRECTIVE -> parse_directive; if non-null append to
    modules_list (directives ride in the same list so the
    preprocessor can find them in source order), then advance
  - otherwise registers "Expected module or directive" and advances
    one token for recovery
Returns the source_file pointer.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse Verilog source file (list of modules and compiler directives).
    @End Reasoning

    Let source_file_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 16

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with source_file_ptr, 0, NODE_SOURCE_FILE

    Let modules_list be proc list_create from ListCore
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with source_file_ptr, 8, modules_list

    Note: Parse modules until EOF
    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_EOF from VerilogLexer:
            Set continue to 0
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_MODULE from VerilogLexer:
                Let module_ptr be proc parse_module with parser_ptr
                proc list_append from ListCore with modules_list, module_ptr
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_DIRECTIVE from VerilogLexer:
                    Note: Parse compiler directive and store in source file
                    Let directive_ptr be proc parse_directive with parser_ptr
                    If directive_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Note: Add directive to source file for preprocessing
                        Note: Directives should be processed before module instantiation
                        proc list_append from ListCore with modules_list, directive_ptr
                    End If
                    proc advance with parser_ptr
                Otherwise:
                    proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Expected module or directive"
                    proc advance with parser_ptr  Note: Skip and continue
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return source_file_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Module Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a full module definition. The grammar is:
  module Name #(param_port_list)? (port_list)? ; module_items endmodule
Both parameter port list and signal port list are optional. The
parser produces a 56-byte NODE_MODULE record carrying the name,
parameter list, port list, and items list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 56 bytes for NODE_MODULE. Writes type @0. Expects 'module'
keyword. Reads name via IDENTIFIER token, writes string @8.
Parameter list: if '#' follows, expects '(' and parses via
parse_parameter_port_list, expects ')'. Always writes a list (empty
if absent) @16. Port list: if '(' follows, parses via
parse_port_list, expects ')'. Writes ports list @24. Expects ';'.
Calls parse_module_items, writes items list @32. Expects
'endmodule'. Returns the module pointer.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_module" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse module definition: module name (ports); ... endmodule
    @End Reasoning

    Let module_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 56

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with module_ptr, 0, NODE_MODULE

    Note: Expect 'module' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_MODULE from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse module name
    Let name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let module_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with name_token, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with module_ptr, 8, module_name

    Note: Parse parameter list if present (optional #(params))
    Let params_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_HASH from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr  Note: Skip #
        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

        Set params_list to proc parse_parameter_port_list with parser_ptr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with module_ptr, 16, params_list

    Note: Parse port list
    Let ports_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr  Note: Skip (

        Set ports_list to proc parse_port_list with parser_ptr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with module_ptr, 24, ports_list

    Note: Expect semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse module items (declarations, statements, etc.)
    Let items_list be proc parse_module_items with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with module_ptr, 32, items_list

    Note: Expect endmodule
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ENDMODULE from VerilogLexer

    Return module_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses the signal port list inside module HeaderName(p1, p2, ...).
At header level we only capture port NAMES; the directions and
widths are filled in by separate port declarations inside the
module body. This matches Verilog-2001 ANSI-style headers as
well as the older non-ANSI form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty list. Loop: expects IDENTIFIER, reads its string
@8, appends to the list. Then checks for ','; if present advances
and continues, otherwise stops. Returns the list.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_port_list" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse comma-separated port list.
    @End Reasoning

    Let ports_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Note: Parse port identifier
        Let port_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
        Let port_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with port_token, 8

        proc list_append from ListCore with ports_list, port_name

        Note: Check for comma (more ports)
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
            proc advance with parser_ptr
        Otherwise:
            Set continue to 0
        End If
    End While

    Return ports_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses the optional #(...) parameter port list that follows the
module name in the module header. Each entry is a full parameter
declaration (with default value). Distinct from parse_port_list
which handles signal ports.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty list. Loop: if next token matches PARAMETER,
calls parse_parameter_declaration and appends the result. Then
checks for ','; if present advance and continue, otherwise stop.
Returns the list.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_parameter_port_list" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse parameter port list in module header.
    @End Reasoning

    Let params_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Note: Parse parameter declaration
        If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_PARAMETER from VerilogLexer:
            Let param_ptr be proc parse_parameter_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with params_list, param_ptr
        End If

        Note: Check for comma
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
            proc advance with parser_ptr
        Otherwise:
            Set continue to 0
        End If
    End While

    Return params_list
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Module Item Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Inside-the-module dispatcher. Verilog has 11 distinct module-level
items (port/net/reg/integer/parameter declarations, always/initial
blocks, continuous assigns, function/task declarations, generate
blocks, and module instantiations). This pass walks token by token
and dispatches to the right sub-parser until 'endmodule'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty items list. Loop while not TOKEN_ENDMODULE:
  - INPUT/OUTPUT/INOUT -> parse_port_declaration
  - WIRE/TRI/SUPPLY0/SUPPLY1 -> parse_net_declaration
  - REG -> parse_reg_declaration
  - INTEGER -> parse_integer_declaration
  - PARAMETER/LOCALPARAM -> parse_parameter_declaration
  - ALWAYS -> parse_always_block
  - INITIAL -> parse_initial_block
  - ASSIGN -> parse_assign_statement
  - FUNCTION -> parse_function_declaration
  - TASK -> parse_task_declaration
  - GENERATE -> parse_generate_block
  - IDENTIFIER -> parse_module_instantiation (an identifier at the
    item level is a module type name)
  - anything else -> "Unexpected module item" error and advance
Each successful parse appends to items_list. Returns items_list.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_module_items" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse module items until endmodule.
    @End Reasoning

    Let items_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENDMODULE from VerilogLexer:
            Set continue to 0
        Otherwise:
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INPUT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_OUTPUT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_INOUT from VerilogLexer:
                Let port_decl be proc parse_port_declaration with parser_ptr
                proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, port_decl
            Otherwise:
                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WIRE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_TRI from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_SUPPLY0 from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_SUPPLY1 from VerilogLexer:
                    Let net_decl be proc parse_net_declaration with parser_ptr
                    proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, net_decl
                Otherwise:
                    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer:
                        Let reg_decl be proc parse_reg_declaration with parser_ptr
                        proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, reg_decl
                    Otherwise:
                        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from VerilogLexer:
                            Let int_decl be proc parse_integer_declaration with parser_ptr
                            proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, int_decl
                        Otherwise:
                            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PARAMETER from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_LOCALPARAM from VerilogLexer:
                                Let param be proc parse_parameter_declaration with parser_ptr
                                proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, param
                            Otherwise:
                                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ALWAYS from VerilogLexer:
                                    Let always_block be proc parse_always_block with parser_ptr
                                    proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, always_block
                                Otherwise:
                                    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INITIAL from VerilogLexer:
                                        Let initial_block be proc parse_initial_block with parser_ptr
                                        proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, initial_block
                                    Otherwise:
                                        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN from VerilogLexer:
                                            Let assign_stmt be proc parse_assign_statement with parser_ptr
                                            proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, assign_stmt
                                        Otherwise:
                                            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FUNCTION from VerilogLexer:
                                                Let func_decl be proc parse_function_declaration with parser_ptr
                                                proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, func_decl
                                            Otherwise:
                                                If token_type is equal to TOKEN_TASK from VerilogLexer:
                                                    Let task_decl be proc parse_task_declaration with parser_ptr
                                                    proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, task_decl
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GENERATE from VerilogLexer:
                                                        Let gen_block be proc parse_generate_block with parser_ptr
                                                        proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, gen_block
                                                    Otherwise:
                                                        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer:
                                                            Note: Module instantiation
                                                            Let inst be proc parse_module_instantiation with parser_ptr
                                                            proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, inst
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                            Note: Unknown item type
                                                            proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Unexpected module item"
                                                            proc advance with parser_ptr
                                                        End If
                                                    End If
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Return items_list
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Declaration Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a port declaration: input/output/inout direction + optional
range + name list. Port declarations inside the module body can
add names not in the original module header port list, so this
parses each name list independently of the header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_PORT_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Advances past the direction token (TOKEN_INPUT/OUTPUT/INOUT) and
writes its type code @8. Optionally parses range when next is '['
and writes range_ptr (or 0) @16. Calls parse_identifier_list,
writes the names list @24. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_port_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse port declaration: input/output/inout [range] name, name, ...;
    @End Reasoning

    Let port_decl_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with port_decl_ptr, 0, NODE_PORT_DECLARATION

    Note: Get port direction
    Let direction_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
    Let direction be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with direction_token, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with port_decl_ptr, 8, direction

    Note: Parse optional range [msb:lsb]
    Let range_ptr be 0

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer:
        Set range_ptr to proc parse_range with parser_ptr
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with port_decl_ptr, 16, range_ptr

    Note: Parse port names (comma-separated)
    Let names_list be proc parse_identifier_list with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with port_decl_ptr, 24, names_list

    Note: Expect semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return port_decl_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog net declaration (wire, tri, supply0, supply1).
Nets are continuously-driven signals - distinct from reg storage.
The specific net_type byte is preserved so later passes can apply
the right driver semantics (supply0/supply1 are 0/1 constants
respectively).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_NET_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Advances past the net-type token and writes net_type @8. Optionally
parses a range when next is '[', writes range pointer (or 0) @16.
Calls parse_identifier_list, writes the names list @24. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_net_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse net declaration: wire/tri/etc. [range] name, name, ...;
    @End Reasoning

    Let net_decl_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with net_decl_ptr, 0, NODE_NET_DECLARATION

    Note: Get net type
    Let net_type_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
    Let net_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with net_type_token, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with net_decl_ptr, 8, net_type

    Note: Parse optional range
    Let range_ptr be 0

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer:
        Set range_ptr to proc parse_range with parser_ptr
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with net_decl_ptr, 16, range_ptr

    Note: Parse net names
    Let names_list be proc parse_identifier_list with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with net_decl_ptr, 24, names_list

    Note: Expect semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return net_decl_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog 'reg' declaration. reg is the storage-element
abstraction (driven by procedural assignments inside always /
initial blocks); semantically distinct from wire (driven by
continuous assignments) even when synthesised to the same gate
output.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for NODE_REG_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Expects TOKEN_REG. Optionally parses a range (when next is '[')
and writes the range pointer (or 0) @8. Calls parse_identifier_list,
writes the names list @16. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_reg_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse reg declaration: reg [range] name, name, ...;
    @End Reasoning

    Let reg_decl_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with reg_decl_ptr, 0, NODE_REG_DECLARATION

    Note: Expect reg keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse optional range
    Let range_ptr be 0

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer:
        Set range_ptr to proc parse_range with parser_ptr
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with reg_decl_ptr, 8, range_ptr

    Note: Parse reg names
    Let names_list be proc parse_identifier_list with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with reg_decl_ptr, 16, names_list

    Note: Expect semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return reg_decl_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog 'integer' declaration. Verilog 'integer' is a
32-bit signed scalar used for loop counters and intermediate
computations in procedural code. Unlike reg, it has no width
modifier (always 32 bits).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_INTEGER_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Expects TOKEN_INTEGER. Calls parse_identifier_list to capture the
comma-separated names, writes the names list @8. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_integer_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse integer declaration: integer name, name, ...;
    @End Reasoning

    Let int_decl_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with int_decl_ptr, 0, NODE_INTEGER_DECLARATION

    Note: Expect integer keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_INTEGER from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse integer names
    Let names_list be proc parse_identifier_list with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with int_decl_ptr, 8, names_list

    Note: Expect semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return int_decl_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses both "parameter" (overridable from outside) and "localparam"
(internally fixed) declarations. The is_local flag distinguishes
them in the AST so downstream code can enforce localparam's
non-overridable semantics.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_PARAMETER. Tries match on TOKEN_LOCALPARAM
- if it consumes, sets is_local = 1; otherwise expects TOKEN_PARAMETER
and is_local stays 0. Writes is_local @8. Expects an IDENTIFIER for
the name and writes its string @16. Expects '=' (TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP).
Parses the RHS via parse_expression and writes @24. Optionally
consumes a trailing ';' (absent in parameter-port-list form).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_parameter_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse parameter declaration: parameter name = value;
    @End Reasoning

    Let param_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with param_ptr, 0, NODE_PARAMETER

    Note: Expect parameter or localparam keyword
    Let is_local be 0
    If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LOCALPARAM from VerilogLexer:
        Set is_local to 1
    Otherwise:
        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_PARAMETER from VerilogLexer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with param_ptr, 8, is_local

    Note: Parse parameter name
    Let name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let param_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with name_token, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with param_ptr, 16, param_name

    Note: Expect = and value
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP from VerilogLexer

    Let value_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with param_ptr, 24, value_expr

    Note: Optional semicolon (not present in parameter port list)
    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
    End If

    Return param_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog [msb:lsb] range expression. Both bounds are full
expressions, not literals, because Verilog permits parameterised
widths like [WIDTH-1:0]. The semantic phase later evaluates these
expressions to compute the actual bit width.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for a two-field range record. Expects '[',
parses msb via parse_expression and writes @0, expects ':', parses
lsb via parse_expression and writes @8, expects ']'. Returns the
range pointer.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_range" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse bit range: [msb:lsb]
    @End Reasoning

    Let range_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer

    Let msb_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with range_ptr, 0, msb_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COLON from VerilogLexer

    Let lsb_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with range_ptr, 8, lsb_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RBRACKET from VerilogLexer

    Return range_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses an identifier1, identifier2, ... sequence into a List of
string pointers. Used by every declaration form (port, net, reg,
integer) where a single declaration line can introduce multiple
names of the same type.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates an empty list. Loop: expect TOKEN_IDENTIFIER, read its
string @8 from the token, append to the list. If next token is
TOKEN_COMMA, advance and continue; otherwise stop. Returns the
list.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_identifier_list" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse comma-separated list of identifiers.
    @End Reasoning

    Let names_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Let name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
        Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with name_token, 8

        proc list_append from ListCore with names_list, name

        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
            proc advance with parser_ptr
        Otherwise:
            Set continue to 0
        End If
    End While

    Return names_list
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog 'reg' or 'integer' local/port variable declaration
that appears inside a function or task body. Verilog uses the same
declaration grammar in these contexts as at module scope, so this
function dispatches to the existing reg/integer declaration parsers
based on the leading keyword rather than duplicating their logic.
This keeps function- and task-local declarations structurally
identical to module-level ones, so downstream HIR translation and
the semantic phase need no special case for declaration scope.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks the current token type. TOKEN_REG delegates to
parse_reg_declaration (which produces a NODE_REG_DECLARATION with
optional range and comma-separated names). TOKEN_INTEGER delegates
to parse_integer_declaration (NODE_INTEGER_DECLARATION, no range).
Any other leading token is a parse error in this context: an error
is recorded and the offending token is consumed so the enclosing
declaration loop makes forward progress instead of spinning, and 0
is returned to signal "no declaration produced".
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_variable_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse a reg or integer variable declaration inside a function/task body.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_reg_declaration with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_integer_declaration with parser_ptr
    End If

    Note: Not a variable declaration keyword - record error and consume
    Note: one token so the caller's declaration loop makes forward progress.
    proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Expected reg or integer declaration"
    proc advance with parser_ptr
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog 'genvar' declaration. genvar declares one or more
elaboration-time integer indices used to drive generate-for loops.
Syntactically it is a keyword followed by a comma-separated list of
identifiers and a terminating semicolon - identical in shape to an
integer declaration, but carries its own node type because genvars
have distinct elaboration-time-only semantics (they do not exist as
runtime hardware) that later passes must treat specially.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_GENVAR_DECLARATION (type @0, names list
@8, reserved @16). Writes the node type @0. Expects the TOKEN_GENVAR
keyword. Delegates to parse_identifier_list to collect the
comma-separated genvar names and writes that list @8. Expects the
terminating ';'. The reserved slot @16 is zeroed so the record has a
deterministic layout for the HIR translator. Returns the node ptr.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_genvar_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse genvar declaration: genvar name, name, ...;
    @End Reasoning

    Let genvar_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with genvar_ptr, 0, NODE_GENVAR_DECLARATION

    Note: Expect genvar keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_GENVAR from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse comma-separated genvar names
    Let names_list be proc parse_identifier_list with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with genvar_ptr, 8, names_list

    Note: Expect terminating semicolon
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with genvar_ptr, 16, 0  Note: reserved field

    Return genvar_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Captures a Verilog compiler directive (`define, `include, `ifdef,
`timescale, etc.) as an AST node so the source-file record retains
the directive text in order. Directives are lexed as a single
TOKEN_DIRECTIVE whose lexeme is the full backtick-prefixed name; the
parser does not expand them (that is a separate preprocessor stage),
it only preserves them so a round-trip emission can re-emit the
directive verbatim and the preprocessor can match exact names.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads - but does not consume - the current token via peek, because
the top-level driver loop advances past the directive itself after
this function returns. If the current token is not a TOKEN_DIRECTIVE
(defensive guard), returns 0 so the driver appends nothing. Otherwise
allocates 24 bytes for NODE_DIRECTIVE (type @0, directive-name string
@8, reserved @16), reads the directive lexeme from offset 8 of the
token record, stores it @8, zeroes the reserved slot @16, and returns
the node pointer.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_directive" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse a compiler directive token into a NODE_DIRECTIVE record.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_ptr be proc peek with parser_ptr
    If token_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let token_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 0
    If token_type is not equal to TOKEN_DIRECTIVE from VerilogLexer:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let directive_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with directive_ptr, 0, NODE_DIRECTIVE

    Note: The directive lexeme (full backtick-prefixed name) is stored
    Note: at offset 8 of the token record by the lexer.
    Let directive_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with directive_ptr, 8, directive_name

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with directive_ptr, 16, 0  Note: reserved field

    Return directive_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Behavioral Block Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses an always block - Verilog's combinational/sequential
behavioural construct. The sensitivity list (optional in pre-2001
syntax, mandatory for synthesisable code) determines whether this
synthesises to combinational logic, latches, or flip-flops.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for NODE_ALWAYS_BLOCK. Writes type @0. Expects
'always'. If next is '@', parses the sensitivity list via
parse_sensitivity_list; otherwise leaves sensitivity pointer as 0.
Writes @8. Parses the body via parse_statement and writes @16.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_always_block" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse always block: always @(sensitivity_list) statement
    @End Reasoning

    Let always_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with always_ptr, 0, NODE_ALWAYS_BLOCK

    Note: Expect always keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ALWAYS from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse sensitivity list
    Let sensitivity_ptr be 0

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_AT from VerilogLexer:
        Set sensitivity_ptr to proc parse_sensitivity_list with parser_ptr
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with always_ptr, 8, sensitivity_ptr

    Note: Parse statement
    Let statement_ptr be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with always_ptr, 16, statement_ptr

    Return always_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses an initial block. Initial blocks run exactly once at time 0
in simulation; they are typically used for testbench setup and are
NOT synthesisable. The AST node carries a single statement (which
may itself be a begin/end block holding many statements).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_INITIAL_BLOCK. Writes type @0. Expects
'initial'. Parses the body via parse_statement and writes @8.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_initial_block" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse initial block: initial statement
    @End Reasoning

    Let initial_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with initial_ptr, 0, NODE_INITIAL_BLOCK

    Note: Expect initial keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_INITIAL from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse statement
    Let statement_ptr be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with initial_ptr, 8, statement_ptr

    Return initial_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog sensitivity list following always @ - the set of
signals whose changes re-trigger the block. Supports the three
common forms: @(posedge X), @(*) (implicit, all read signals), and
@(a or b or c). Each signal entry preserves the optional posedge/
negedge edge specifier so synthesis can build the right flip-flop.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_SENSITIVITY_LIST. Writes type @0.
Expects '@' '('. If next is '*', advances and inserts "*" as a
sentinel into signals_list. Otherwise loops: optionally consumes
posedge/negedge, expects IDENTIFIER, allocates a 24-byte signal_info
record with name @0, is_posedge @8, is_negedge @16, and appends it
to signals_list. Between entries accepts either 'or' keyword or
comma. Writes signals_list @8. Expects ')'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_sensitivity_list" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse sensitivity list: @(posedge clk) or @(*) or @(a or b or c)
    @End Reasoning

    Let sensitivity_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with sensitivity_ptr, 0, NODE_SENSITIVITY_LIST

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_AT from VerilogLexer

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let signals_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Check for @(*)
    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_STAR from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr
        proc list_append from ListCore with signals_list, "*"  Note: All signals
    Otherwise:
        Note: Parse individual signals
        Let continue be 1

        While continue is equal to 1:
            Note: Check for edge specifiers
            Let is_posedge be 0
            Let is_negedge be 0

            If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_POSEDGE from VerilogLexer:
                Set is_posedge to 1
            Otherwise:
                If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_NEGEDGE from VerilogLexer:
                    Set is_negedge to 1
                End If
            End If

            Note: Parse signal name
            Let signal_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
            Let signal_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with signal_token, 8

            Note: Add signal with edge info
            Let signal_info_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with signal_info_ptr, 0, signal_name
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with signal_info_ptr, 8, is_posedge
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with signal_info_ptr, 16, is_negedge

            proc list_append from ListCore with signals_list, signal_info_ptr

            Note: Check for 'or' keyword or comma
            Let has_or be proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_OR from VerilogLexer
            Let has_comma be proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer
            If has_or is equal to 1 or has_comma is equal to 1:
                Note: Continue parsing
            Otherwise:
                Set continue to 0
            End If
        End While
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with sensitivity_ptr, 8, signals_list

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Return sensitivity_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Statement Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Procedural-statement dispatcher. Routes based on the leading token
to the correct statement-specific sub-parser. Used inside always /
initial blocks and inside nested statement contexts (then/else
branches, loop bodies, case items).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads peek_type. Dispatches:
  - BEGIN -> parse_begin_end_block
  - IF -> parse_if_statement
  - CASE / CASEX / CASEZ -> parse_case_statement
  - FOR -> parse_for_loop
  - WHILE -> parse_while_loop
  - SYSTEM_TASK -> parse_system_task_call
  - IDENTIFIER -> parse_assignment_or_call (ambiguous lookahead
    handled inside that helper)
  - anything else -> registers "Expected statement" error and
    returns 0
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_statement" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse any statement (assignment, if, case, loop, block, etc.).
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_BEGIN from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_begin_end_block with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IF from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_if_statement with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CASE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_CASEX from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_CASEZ from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_case_statement with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOR from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_for_loop with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WHILE from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_while_loop with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_SYSTEM_TASK from VerilogLexer:
        Return proc parse_system_task_call with parser_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer:
        Note: Assignment or function call
        Return proc parse_assignment_or_call with parser_ptr
    End If

    Note: Unknown statement
    proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Expected statement"
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a begin/end statement-group block. begin..end is Verilog's
braced statement container, used to group multiple statements where
the grammar expects a single statement (e.g. then-branch of an if).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_BEGIN_END_BLOCK. Writes type @0. Expects
'begin'. Loops parsing statements until it sees TOKEN_END;
appending each via parse_statement to statements_list. Writes the
list @8. Expects 'end'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_begin_end_block" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse begin...end block: begin statements... end
    @End Reasoning

    Let block_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block_ptr, 0, NODE_BEGIN_END_BLOCK

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_BEGIN from VerilogLexer

    Let statements_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_END from VerilogLexer:
            Set continue to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let stmt_ptr be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with statements_list, stmt_ptr
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block_ptr, 8, statements_list

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_END from VerilogLexer

    Return block_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses procedural if/else. Verilog's if-without-else has the classic
dangling-else ambiguity; the grammar (and this parser) resolve it
greedy-left: each 'else' binds to the nearest preceding 'if'. This
is implicit in the recursive descent because parse_statement on the
then-branch eagerly consumes any nested 'else'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_IF_STATEMENT. Writes type @0. Expects
'if' '('. Parses condition via parse_expression, writes @8.
Expects ')'. Parses then via parse_statement, writes @16. Optional
'else' (via match): if present, parses else-statement via
parse_statement and writes @24; otherwise leaves @24 as 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_if_statement" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse if statement: if (condition) statement else statement
    @End Reasoning

    Let if_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with if_ptr, 0, NODE_IF_STATEMENT

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IF from VerilogLexer

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let condition_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with if_ptr, 8, condition_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let then_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with if_ptr, 16, then_stmt

    Note: Optional else clause
    Let else_stmt be 0

    If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ELSE from VerilogLexer:
        Set else_stmt to proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with if_ptr, 24, else_stmt

    Return if_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses Verilog case / casex / casez statements. The variants differ
in how unknown bits in the case items are treated: casex treats x/z
as don't-cares; casez treats z as don't-care; case requires exact
match. The case_type byte preserved on the AST lets the synthesis
backend emit the correct comparison.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_CASE_STATEMENT. Writes type @0. Captures
the case-variant token type into @8. Expects '(' selector ')'.
Parses the selector expression and writes @16. Then loops parsing
case items: each is either an expression list followed by ':' and a
statement, OR "default :" + statement. Items are accumulated in a
list. Expects 'endcase'. Writes the items list into the case
record.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_case_statement" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse case statement: case (expr) item: stmt ... endcase
    @End Reasoning

    Let case_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with case_ptr, 0, NODE_CASE_STATEMENT

    Note: Get case type (case, casex, casez)
    Let case_type_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
    Let case_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with case_type_token, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with case_ptr, 8, case_type

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let selector_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with case_ptr, 16, selector_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse case items
    Let items_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Let continue be 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_ENDCASE from VerilogLexer:
            Set continue to 0
        Otherwise:
            Note: Parse case item (value_expr : statement)
            Let item_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

            If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_DEFAULT from VerilogLexer:
                Note: Default case
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with item_ptr, 0, 0  Note: Null value indicates default
            Otherwise:
                Note: Normal case item
                Let value_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with item_ptr, 0, value_expr
            End If

            proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COLON from VerilogLexer

            Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with item_ptr, 8, stmt

            proc list_append from ListCore with items_list, item_ptr
        End If
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with case_ptr, 24, items_list

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ENDCASE from VerilogLexer

    Return case_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a C-style for loop with init, condition, and update slots.
init and update are assignment statements; condition is an
expression. Used for both bounded iteration in testbenches and for
generate-loop indices in synthesis.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 48 bytes for NODE_FOR_LOOP. Writes type @0. Expects 'for'
'('. Parses init via parse_assignment_or_call (which expects its
own ';'), writes @8. Expects another ';'. Parses condition via
parse_expression, writes @16. Expects ';'. Parses update via
parse_assignment_or_call, writes @24. Expects ')'. Parses body via
parse_statement, writes @32.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_for_loop" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse for loop: for (init; condition; update) statement
    @End Reasoning

    Let for_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 48

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with for_ptr, 0, NODE_FOR_LOOP

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_FOR from VerilogLexer

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse initialization
    Let init_stmt be proc parse_assignment_or_call with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with for_ptr, 8, init_stmt

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse condition
    Let condition_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with for_ptr, 16, condition_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse update
    Let update_stmt be proc parse_assignment_or_call with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with for_ptr, 24, update_stmt

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse loop body
    Let body_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with for_ptr, 32, body_stmt

    Return for_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a procedural while-loop. Used inside always / initial blocks
to model iterative behaviour. The condition is a full expression
(typically a bit check or counter compare); the body is a single
statement (may be a begin/end block).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for NODE_WHILE_LOOP. Writes type @0. Expects
'while' '('. Parses condition via parse_expression, writes @8.
Expects ')'. Parses body via parse_statement, writes @16.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_while_loop" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse while loop: while (condition) statement
    @End Reasoning

    Let while_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with while_ptr, 0, NODE_WHILE_LOOP

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_WHILE from VerilogLexer

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let condition_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with while_ptr, 8, condition_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let body_stmt be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with while_ptr, 16, body_stmt

    Return while_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Disambiguator: when a statement begins with an identifier, it could
be a blocking assignment (lhs = rhs;), a non-blocking assignment
(lhs <= rhs;), or a bare expression statement (task call /
function call). The LHS is parsed first as a primary expression and
then we look at what follows.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses LHS via parse_primary_expression. Peeks the next token type:
  - TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP -> advance, allocate NODE_BLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT
    (32 bytes), write type @0, lhs @8, rhs (via parse_expression)
    @16. Expects ';'.
  - TOKEN_NONBLOCKING_ASSIGN -> advance, allocate
    NODE_NONBLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT (32 bytes), same field layout but
    different node type tag.
  - else -> expects ';' and returns the lhs_expr unchanged
    (treating it as a standalone expression statement, used for
    task/function calls that don't return values).
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_assignment_or_call" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse assignment (blocking or non-blocking) or task call.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Parse left-hand side (identifier with optional indexing)
    Let lhs_expr be proc parse_primary_expression with parser_ptr

    Note: Check for assignment operator
    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP from VerilogLexer:
        Note: Blocking assignment
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let assign_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 0, NODE_BLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 8, lhs_expr

        Let rhs_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 16, rhs_expr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

        Return assign_ptr
    End If

    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NONBLOCKING_ASSIGN from VerilogLexer:
        Note: Non-blocking assignment
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Set assign_ptr to proc allocate from Memory with 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 0, NODE_NONBLOCKING_ASSIGNMENT
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 8, lhs_expr

        Set rhs_expr to proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 16, rhs_expr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

        Return assign_ptr
    End If

    Note: Not an assignment, return as expression statement
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer
    Return lhs_expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a $-prefixed system task call ($display, $monitor, $finish,
etc.). The lexer emits TOKEN_SYSTEM_TASK for any $name; this parser
captures the name and optional argument list. Arguments are full
expressions because system tasks accept format strings followed by
any number of value expressions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for NODE_SYSTEM_TASK_CALL. Writes type @0.
Expects TOKEN_SYSTEM_TASK; reads its name string @8 from the token
and writes onto the node @8. Argument list is OPTIONAL - if next
token is '(', parses comma-separated expressions into args_list
until ')'. Writes args_list @16. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_system_task_call" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse system task call: $display(...); $monitor(...);
    @End Reasoning

    Let call_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with call_ptr, 0, NODE_SYSTEM_TASK_CALL

    Note: Get system task name
    Let task_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SYSTEM_TASK from VerilogLexer
    Let task_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with task_token, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with call_ptr, 8, task_name

    Note: Parse arguments (optional)
    Let args_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer:
        Note: Parse argument list
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is not equal to TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer:
            Let continue be 1

            While continue is equal to 1:
                Let arg_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
                proc list_append from ListCore with args_list, arg_expr

                If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
                    Note: More arguments
                Otherwise:
                    Set continue to 0
                End If
            End While
        End If

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with call_ptr, 16, args_list

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return call_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Other Declaration Parsing
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Parses a continuous-assignment 'assign' module item. Continuous
assignments drive nets (typically wires) and are evaluated whenever
their RHS changes - distinct from procedural blocking/non-blocking
assignments which run inside always/initial blocks.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for NODE_ASSIGN. Writes type @0. Expects 'assign'.
Parses LHS via parse_primary_expression (continuous assigns can only
target identifier-shaped lvalues with optional bit/part select).
Expects '=' (TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP). Parses RHS via parse_expression.
Writes lhs @8 and rhs @16. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_assign_statement" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse continuous assignment: assign lhs = rhs;
    @End Reasoning

    Let assign_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 0, NODE_ASSIGN

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ASSIGN from VerilogLexer

    Let lhs_expr be proc parse_primary_expression with parser_ptr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ASSIGN_OP from VerilogLexer

    Let rhs_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 8, lhs_expr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with assign_ptr, 16, rhs_expr

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return assign_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a child-module instantiation inside a module body. Verilog
distinguishes module declaration (with 'module' keyword) from
instantiation (just the module type name followed by an instance
name). Optional parameter overrides via #(...) and the port
connection list complete the construct.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 48 bytes for NODE_MODULE_INSTANTIATION. Writes type @0.
Reads module_name via IDENTIFIER token, writes string @8.
If '#' (TOKEN_HASH) follows, expects '(' and parses
comma-separated parameter expressions into params_list, then ')'.
Always writes params_list @16. Reads instance name via IDENTIFIER,
writes string @24. Expects '('; parses comma-separated port
connection expressions into ports_list. Expects ')'. Writes
ports_list @32. Expects ';'.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_module_instantiation" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse module instantiation: module_name #(params) instance_name (ports);
    @End Reasoning

    Let inst_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 48

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with inst_ptr, 0, NODE_MODULE_INSTANTIATION

    Note: Module name
    Let module_name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let module_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module_name_token, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with inst_ptr, 8, module_name

    Note: Optional parameter override #(...)
    Let params_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_HASH from VerilogLexer:
        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

        Note: Parse parameter assignments
        Let continue be 1

        While continue is equal to 1:
            Let param_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with params_list, param_expr

            If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
                Note: More parameters
            Otherwise:
                Set continue to 0
            End If
        End While

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with inst_ptr, 16, params_list

    Note: Instance name
    Let inst_name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let inst_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with inst_name_token, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with inst_ptr, 24, inst_name

    Note: Port connections
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer

    Let ports_list be proc list_create from ListCore

    Note: Parse port connections
    Set continue to 1

    While continue is equal to 1:
        Let port_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
        proc list_append from ListCore with ports_list, port_expr

        If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
            Note: More ports
        Otherwise:
            Set continue to 0
        End If
    End While

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with inst_ptr, 32, ports_list

    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Return inst_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog function declaration. Functions differ from tasks
in that they: must return a single value (specified by an optional
return-type range), cannot have inout/output ports (only input),
and complete in zero simulation time (no #/wait delays in body).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 48 bytes for NODE_FUNCTION_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Expects 'function'. Optional range after function keyword becomes
return_type @8. Expects IDENTIFIER for function name; reads its
string @8 from the token and writes onto the node @16. Expects ';'.
Loops parsing input declarations and reg/integer locals into
'declarations' list; loop exits when next token isn't a declaration
keyword. Writes declarations @24. Parses body (begin/end or single
statement) and writes @32. Expects 'endfunction'. Reserved slot
@40 = 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_function_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse Verilog function declaration with return type, name, input/output ports, and body.
    Functions in Verilog: function [range] name; input declarations; statements endfunction
    @End Reasoning

    Let func_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 48

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 0, NODE_FUNCTION_DECLARATION

    Note: Expect 'function' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_FUNCTION from VerilogLexer

    Note: Optional return type/range [7:0]
    Let return_type be 0
    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer:
        Set return_type to proc parse_range with parser_ptr
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 8, return_type

    Note: Function name (identifier)
    Let name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let func_name be 0
    If name_token is not equal to 0:
        Set func_name to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with name_token, 8
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 16, func_name

    Note: Expect semicolon after function name
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse function input/output declarations
    Let declarations be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

        Note: Check for input/output declarations
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INPUT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_OUTPUT from VerilogLexer:
            Let port_decl be proc parse_port_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, port_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Check for reg/integer declarations
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from VerilogLexer:
            Let var_decl be proc parse_variable_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, var_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: No more declarations
        Break
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 24, declarations

    Note: Parse function body (begin...end or single statement)
    Let body be 0
    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_BEGIN from VerilogLexer:
        Set body to proc parse_begin_end_block with parser_ptr
    Otherwise:
        Note: Single statement body
        Set body to proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 32, body

    Note: Expect 'endfunction' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ENDFUNCTION from VerilogLexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with func_ptr, 40, 0  Note: reserved field

    Return func_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog task declaration. Tasks are subroutines that may
have input/output/inout ports, may contain timing controls (#/wait),
and do not return a value. The body parser collects all statements
until 'endtask' rather than expecting a single statement.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 40 bytes for NODE_TASK_DECLARATION. Writes type @0.
Expects 'task'. Reads task_name from IDENTIFIER token and writes @8.
Expects ';'. Loops parsing input/output/inout declarations and
reg/integer locals into 'declarations' list; loop exits when the
next token is not a declaration keyword. Writes declarations @16.
Parses body: if next is 'begin' delegates to parse_begin_end_block;
otherwise accumulates statements until 'endtask'. Writes body @24.
Expects 'endtask'. Reserved slot @32 = 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_task_declaration" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse Verilog task declaration with name, input/output/inout ports, and body.
    Tasks in Verilog: task name; input/output/inout declarations; statements endtask
    @End Reasoning

    Let task_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with task_ptr, 0, NODE_TASK_DECLARATION

    Note: Expect 'task' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_TASK from VerilogLexer

    Note: Task name (identifier)
    Let name_token be proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer
    Let task_name be 0
    If name_token is not equal to 0:
        Set task_name to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with name_token, 8
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with task_ptr, 8, task_name

    Note: Expect semicolon after task name
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_SEMICOLON from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse task input/output/inout declarations
    Let declarations be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

        Note: Check for input/output/inout declarations
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_INPUT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_OUTPUT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_INOUT from VerilogLexer:
            Let port_decl be proc parse_port_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, port_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Check for reg/integer declarations
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_INTEGER from VerilogLexer:
            Let var_decl be proc parse_variable_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with declarations, var_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: No more declarations
        Break
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with task_ptr, 16, declarations

    Note: Parse task body (begin...end or statement sequence)
    Let body be 0
    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_BEGIN from VerilogLexer:
        Set body to proc parse_begin_end_block with parser_ptr
    Otherwise:
        Note: Statement sequence body
        Let statements be proc list_create from ListCore

        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr

            Note: Stop at endtask
            If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENDTASK from VerilogLexer:
                Break
            End If

            Note: Parse statement
            Let stmt be proc parse_statement with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with statements, stmt
        End While

        Set body to statements
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with task_ptr, 24, body

    Note: Expect 'endtask' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ENDTASK from VerilogLexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with task_ptr, 32, 0  Note: reserved field

    Return task_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Parses a Verilog generate block. Generate blocks are evaluated at
elaboration time to conditionally instantiate hardware - allowing
parameterised module structures (e.g. N copies of a sub-module
selected by a genvar loop). Permitted items: genvar declarations,
for/if/case constructs, module instantiations, and net/parameter
declarations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 24 bytes for NODE_GENERATE_BLOCK. Writes type @0. Expects
'generate'. Loops until TOKEN_ENDGENERATE, dispatching:
  - GENVAR -> parse_genvar_declaration
  - FOR -> parse_for_loop (generate-for has the same syntax as the
    procedural for loop)
  - IF -> parse_if_statement (generate-if uses statement syntax)
  - CASE -> parse_case_statement
  - IDENTIFIER -> parse_module_instantiation
  - PARAMETER -> parse_parameter_declaration
  - WIRE / REG -> parse_net_declaration
  - anything else -> advance one token (defensive infinite-loop
    guard)
Writes items list @8. Expects 'endgenerate'. Reserved @16 = 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_generate_block" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse Verilog generate block with conditional instantiation, loops, and case statements.
    Generate blocks: generate genvar/for/if/case...module instantiations...endgenerate
    @End Reasoning

    Let gen_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with gen_ptr, 0, NODE_GENERATE_BLOCK

    Note: Expect 'generate' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_GENERATE from VerilogLexer

    Note: Parse generate items (genvar, for, if, case, declarations, instantiations)
    Let items be proc list_create from ListCore

    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

        Note: Check for end of generate block
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_ENDGENERATE from VerilogLexer:
            Break
        End If

        Note: Parse genvar declaration
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_GENVAR from VerilogLexer:
            Let genvar_decl be proc parse_genvar_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, genvar_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse generate for loop
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_FOR from VerilogLexer:
            Let for_loop be proc parse_for_loop with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, for_loop
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse generate if statement
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IF from VerilogLexer:
            Let if_stmt be proc parse_if_statement with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, if_stmt
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse generate case statement
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_CASE from VerilogLexer:
            Let case_stmt be proc parse_case_statement with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, case_stmt
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse module instantiation
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer:
            Let inst be proc parse_module_instantiation with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, inst
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Parse other declarations (parameter, wire, reg)
        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PARAMETER from VerilogLexer:
            Let param_decl be proc parse_parameter_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, param_decl
            Continue
        End If

        If token_type is equal to TOKEN_WIRE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_REG from VerilogLexer:
            Let net_decl be proc parse_net_declaration with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with items, net_decl
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Unknown item - skip token to avoid infinite loop
        proc advance with parser_ptr
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with gen_ptr, 8, items

    Note: Expect 'endgenerate' keyword
    proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_ENDGENERATE from VerilogLexer

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with gen_ptr, 16, 0  Note: reserved field

    Return gen_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Expression Parsing (with precedence)
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Public entry point for any expression parse. Doesn't itself
implement any operator handling - just delegates to the top of the
precedence cascade (the ternary level). Centralising this delegation
in a named function lets callers say parse_expression() without
having to know the precedence root.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Direct tail-call to parse_conditional_expression. The conditional
is the lowest-precedence binary form in Verilog so it sits at the
top of the cascade.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse expression with operator precedence (start with conditional/ternary).
    @End Reasoning

    Return proc parse_conditional_expression with parser_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Top of the precedence cascade. Verilog's ternary "cond ? then :
else" sits above logical-OR. The branches are parsed via the full
parse_expression so they can themselves be ternaries (right-
associative chaining produces a ? b : (c ? d : e)).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses the condition via parse_logical_or_expression. If next token
is TOKEN_QUESTION, allocates a 40-byte NODE_CONDITIONAL_EXPR:
type @0, cond @8, then @16, else @24. Parses then-expr via
parse_expression, expects ':' via expect, parses else-expr via
parse_expression. Returns the conditional node. If no '?' at the
front, returns the unguarded left expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_conditional_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse ternary conditional: expr ? expr : expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let expr be proc parse_logical_or_expression with parser_ptr

    If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_QUESTION from VerilogLexer:
        Let cond_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 40
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cond_ptr, 0, NODE_CONDITIONAL_EXPR
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cond_ptr, 8, expr

        Let then_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cond_ptr, 16, then_expr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COLON from VerilogLexer

        Let else_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cond_ptr, 24, else_expr

        Return cond_ptr
    End If

    Return expr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative logical-OR parser ('||'). Below the conditional/
ternary level and above logical-AND in precedence.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_logical_and_expression. Loop while peek_type
== TOKEN_LOGICAL_OR: advance, parse right via
parse_logical_and_expression, build binop, reassign left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_logical_or_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse logical OR: expr || expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser_ptr

    While proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LOGICAL_OR from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_logical_and_expression with parser_ptr

        Let _tok_0 be TOKEN_LOGICAL_OR from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_0, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative logical-AND parser ('&&'). Sits between
logical-OR (above) and bitwise-OR (below). Logical AND evaluates
operand truthiness rather than bit-by-bit AND - that distinction is
in semantic analysis, not in this parser.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_bitwise_or_expression. Loop while peek_type
== TOKEN_LOGICAL_AND: advance, parse right via
parse_bitwise_or_expression, build binop, reassign left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_logical_and_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse logical AND: expr && expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_or_expression with parser_ptr

    While proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LOGICAL_AND from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_or_expression with parser_ptr

        Let _tok_1 be TOKEN_LOGICAL_AND from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_1, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative bitwise-OR parser ('|'). Sits between logical-AND
(above) and bitwise-XOR (below).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_bitwise_xor_expression. Loop while peek_type
== TOKEN_PIPE: advance, parse right via parse_bitwise_xor_expression,
build binop, reassign left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_bitwise_or_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse bitwise OR: expr | expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_xor_expression with parser_ptr

    While proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_PIPE from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_xor_expression with parser_ptr

        Let _tok_2 be TOKEN_PIPE from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_2, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative bitwise-XOR parser ('^'). Sits between bitwise-OR
(above) and bitwise-AND (below). Same operator token is also used
for the binary XNOR (^~ / ~^), but those forms are lexed as
distinct tokens at parse_unary_expression's level for unary
reduction.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_bitwise_and_expression. Loop while peek_type
== TOKEN_CARET: advance, parse right via parse_bitwise_and_expression,
build binop, reassign left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_bitwise_xor_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse bitwise XOR: expr bitwise xor expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_bitwise_and_expression with parser_ptr

    While proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_CARET from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_bitwise_and_expression with parser_ptr

        Let _tok_3 be TOKEN_CARET from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_3, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative single-token operator parser for bitwise AND ('&').
Sits between bitwise-XOR (above in precedence) and equality (below).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_equality_expression. Loop while peek_type ==
TOKEN_AMPERSAND: advance, parse right via parse_equality_expression,
build binop, reassign left. Note: token name AMPERSAND is reused for
the unary reduction-and operator at parse_unary_expression's level;
no conflict because precedence-driven recursion has already
consumed reduction-ands before reaching here.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_bitwise_and_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse bitwise AND: expr bitwise and expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_equality_expression with parser_ptr

    While proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_AMPERSAND from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_equality_expression with parser_ptr

        Let _tok_4 be TOKEN_AMPERSAND from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_4, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative equality-operator parser. Verilog has FOUR forms:
== / != (logical equality, with x/z values yielding x), and the
"case equality" === / !== which treat x and z as ordinary bit
values for exact-match comparison. The lexer distinguishes them; we
treat all four at the same precedence here.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_relational_expression. Caches EQ, NE,
CASE_EQ, CASE_NE token constants. Standard loop with _is_eq_op flag
recomputed each iteration against the four constants. On match:
capture op_type, advance, parse right via
parse_relational_expression, build binop, reassign to left.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_equality_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse equality: expr == expr, expr != expr, expr === expr, expr !== expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_relational_expression with parser_ptr

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Let _eq_tok be TOKEN_EQ from VerilogLexer
    Let _ne_tok be TOKEN_NE from VerilogLexer
    Let _ceq_tok be TOKEN_CASE_EQ from VerilogLexer
    Let _cne_tok be TOKEN_CASE_NE from VerilogLexer
    Let _is_eq_op be 0
    If token_type is equal to _eq_tok:
        Set _is_eq_op to 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to _ne_tok:
        Set _is_eq_op to 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to _ceq_tok:
        Set _is_eq_op to 1
    End If
    If token_type is equal to _cne_tok:
        Set _is_eq_op to 1
    End If
    While _is_eq_op is equal to 1:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_relational_expression with parser_ptr

        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with op_type, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr

        Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr
        Set _is_eq_op to 0
        If token_type is equal to _eq_tok:
            Set _is_eq_op to 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to _ne_tok:
            Set _is_eq_op to 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to _ceq_tok:
            Set _is_eq_op to 1
        End If
        If token_type is equal to _cne_tok:
            Set _is_eq_op to 1
        End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative comparison-operator parser at the relational level
(<, >, <=, >=). Sits between shift and equality in the precedence
cascade.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_shift_expression. Caches LT, GT, LE, GE
token constants. Tests _is_rel_op flag. Standard loop: capture
op_type on match, advance, parse right via parse_shift_expression,
build binop, reassign to left. Recomputes _is_rel_op against the
four constants each iteration so the loop exits on the first
non-relational token.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_relational_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse relational: expr < expr, expr > expr, expr < or equal to expr, expr > or equal to expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_shift_expression with parser_ptr

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Let _lt_tok be TOKEN_LT from VerilogLexer
    Let _gt_tok be TOKEN_GT from VerilogLexer
    Let _le_tok be TOKEN_LE from VerilogLexer
    Let _ge_tok be TOKEN_GE from VerilogLexer
    Let _is_rel_op be 0
    If token_type is equal to _lt_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _gt_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _le_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _ge_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
    While _is_rel_op is equal to 1:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_shift_expression with parser_ptr

        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with op_type, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr

        Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr
        Set _is_rel_op to 0
        If token_type is equal to _lt_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _gt_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _le_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _ge_tok: Set _is_rel_op to 1 End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative shift-operator parser. Verilog has FOUR shift
operators distinguishing logical vs arithmetic on the right:
<<, >>, <<<, >>>. The latter two preserve the sign bit on right
shift / fill with the sign on left shift for signed operands.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_additive_expression. Caches LSHIFT, RSHIFT,
ARITH_LSHIFT, ARITH_RSHIFT token constants and an _is_shift flag.
Standard left-associative loop: rebuild _is_shift each iteration
from peek vs the four constants. On match: capture op_type,
advance, parse right via parse_additive_expression, build binop,
reassign to left. Returns left at exit.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_shift_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse shift: expr shifted left by expr, expr shifted right by expr, expr <<< expr, expr >>> expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_additive_expression with parser_ptr

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Let _ls_tok be TOKEN_LSHIFT from VerilogLexer
    Let _rs_tok be TOKEN_RSHIFT from VerilogLexer
    Let _als_tok be TOKEN_ARITH_LSHIFT from VerilogLexer
    Let _ars_tok be TOKEN_ARITH_RSHIFT from VerilogLexer
    Let _is_shift be 0
    If token_type is equal to _ls_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _rs_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _als_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _ars_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
    While _is_shift is equal to 1:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_additive_expression with parser_ptr

        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with op_type, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr

        Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr
        Set _is_shift to 0
        If token_type is equal to _ls_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _rs_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _als_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _ars_tok: Set _is_shift to 1 End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative + / - parser. Sits between shift and multiplicative
in the precedence cascade. The tokens TOKEN_PLUS / TOKEN_MINUS at
this layer are binary additive ops; the same token bytes used as
unary signs are consumed earlier in parse_unary_expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_multiplicative_expression. Caches plus/minus
token constants. Loop while peek is one of them: capture op_type,
advance, parse right via parse_multiplicative_expression, build a
binop, reassign to left. Returns left at exit.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_additive_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse addition/subtraction: expr + expr, expr - expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser_ptr

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Let _plus_tok be TOKEN_PLUS from VerilogLexer
    Let _minus_tok be TOKEN_MINUS from VerilogLexer
    Let _is_add be 0
    If token_type is equal to _plus_tok: Set _is_add to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _minus_tok: Set _is_add to 1 End If
    While _is_add is equal to 1:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_multiplicative_expression with parser_ptr

        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with op_type, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr

        Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr
        Set _is_add to 0
        If token_type is equal to _plus_tok: Set _is_add to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _minus_tok: Set _is_add to 1 End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Left-associative binary parser at the multiplicative precedence
level. Standard while-loop pattern that handles *, /, % in
sequence at the same precedence.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_power_expression. Caches the three operator
tokens. Loop: while the current token is one of TOKEN_STAR /
TOKEN_SLASH / TOKEN_PERCENT, capture op_type, advance, parse the
right operand via parse_power_expression, build a binop via
create_binary_op, and assign back to left for the left-associative
chaining. Returns left when no more multiplicative operators.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_multiplicative_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse multiplication/division/modulo: expr * expr, expr / expr, expr % expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_power_expression with parser_ptr

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Let _star_tok be TOKEN_STAR from VerilogLexer
    Let _slash_tok be TOKEN_SLASH from VerilogLexer
    Let _pct_tok be TOKEN_PERCENT from VerilogLexer
    Let _is_mul be 0
    If token_type is equal to _star_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _slash_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
    If token_type is equal to _pct_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
    While _is_mul is equal to 1:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_power_expression with parser_ptr

        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with op_type, left, right
        Set left to bin_op_ptr

        Set token_type to proc peek_type with parser_ptr
        Set _is_mul to 0
        If token_type is equal to _star_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _slash_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
        If token_type is equal to _pct_tok: Set _is_mul to 1 End If
    End While

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verilog's '**' exponentiation operator is RIGHT-associative (unlike
most binary operators) so this parser recurses on the right operand
rather than looping. Slots between unary and multiplicative in the
precedence cascade.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Parses left via parse_unary_expression. If next token is
TOKEN_POWER, advances and recursively calls parse_power_expression
for the right operand (giving right-associative chains like
a**b**c parsing as a**(b**c)). Builds the binop and returns. If
not '**' returns left as-is.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_power_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse power: expr ** expr
    @End Reasoning

    Let left be proc parse_unary_expression with parser_ptr

    If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_POWER from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let right be proc parse_power_expression with parser_ptr  Note: Right associative

        Let _tok_5 be TOKEN_POWER from VerilogLexer
        Let bin_op_ptr be proc create_binary_op with _tok_5, left, right
        Return bin_op_ptr
    End If

    Return left
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles prefix unary operators plus Verilog's reduction operators
(unary &, |, ^, ~&, ~|, ~^, ^~ - these collapse a vector into a
single bit). Unary is right-associative: -!~x means -(!(~x)), which
falls out naturally from the recursive call to parse_unary_expression
on the operand.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks the token type. If it matches one of the 11 unary operators
(+, -, !, ~, &, |, ^, ~&, ~|, ~^, ^~), advances past it,
recursively parses the operand via parse_unary_expression, then
allocates a 24-byte NODE_UNARY_OP record: type @0, op_type @8,
operand @16. If no unary operator at the front, delegates to
parse_primary_expression.
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_unary_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse unary operators: +, -, !, ~, &, |, ^, ~&, ~|, ~^, ^~
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Note: Check for unary operators
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_PLUS from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_MINUS from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_LOGICAL_NOT from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_AMPERSAND from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_PIPE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE_AMPERSAND from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE_PIPE from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_TILDE_CARET from VerilogLexer or token_type is equal to TOKEN_CARET_TILDE from VerilogLexer:
        Let op_type be token_type
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let operand be proc parse_unary_expression with parser_ptr

        Let unary_op_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with unary_op_ptr, 0, NODE_UNARY_OP
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with unary_op_ptr, 8, op_type
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with unary_op_ptr, 16, operand

        Return unary_op_ptr
    End If

    Return proc parse_primary_expression with parser_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning:
Atom-level parser for the expression grammar. Handles all leaf forms
(numbers, strings, identifiers with optional bit/part select),
grouped expressions (parens), and brace-delimited concatenations.
This is the recursive base case for the precedence cascade and the
exit point where the parser converts a token into an AST node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads peek_type and dispatches:
  - TOKEN_NUMBER -> builds NODE_NUMBER from the token value
  - TOKEN_STRING -> builds NODE_STRING_LITERAL
  - TOKEN_IDENTIFIER -> builds NODE_IDENTIFIER, then if followed by
    '[' allocates a NODE_BIT_SELECT or NODE_PART_SELECT depending on
    whether a ':' appears between the bracket expressions
  - TOKEN_LPAREN -> recurses into parse_expression and expects ')'
  - TOKEN_LBRACE -> parses a comma-separated list into a
    NODE_CONCATENATION
  - anything else -> registers "Expected primary expression" via
    add_parse_error and returns 0
@End Implementation
Process called "parse_primary_expression" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parse primary expressions: identifiers, numbers, strings, parenthesized expressions, concatenations.
    @End Reasoning

    Let token_type be proc peek_type with parser_ptr

    Note: Number literal
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_NUMBER from VerilogLexer:
        Let number_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
        Let number_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with number_token, 8

        Let number_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with number_ptr, 0, NODE_NUMBER
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with number_ptr, 8, number_value

        Return number_ptr
    End If

    Note: String literal
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_STRING from VerilogLexer:
        Let string_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
        Let string_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with string_token, 16

        Let string_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with string_ptr, 0, NODE_STRING_LITERAL
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with string_ptr, 8, string_value

        Return string_ptr
    End If

    Note: Identifier (with optional bit select or part select)
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_IDENTIFIER from VerilogLexer:
        Let id_token be proc advance with parser_ptr
        Let id_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with id_token, 8

        Let id_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with id_ptr, 0, NODE_IDENTIFIER
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with id_ptr, 8, id_name

        Note: Check for bit select [index] or part select [msb:lsb]
        If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_LBRACKET from VerilogLexer:
            proc advance with parser_ptr  Note: Skip [

            Let index_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr

            Note: Check for part select (colon)
            If proc peek_type with parser_ptr is equal to TOKEN_COLON from VerilogLexer:
                proc advance with parser_ptr  Note: Skip :

                Let lsb_expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr

                proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RBRACKET from VerilogLexer

                Note: Create part select node
                Let part_select_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with part_select_ptr, 0, NODE_PART_SELECT
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with part_select_ptr, 8, id_ptr
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with part_select_ptr, 16, index_expr  Note: MSB
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with part_select_ptr, 24, lsb_expr

                Return part_select_ptr
            Otherwise:
                proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RBRACKET from VerilogLexer

                Note: Create bit select node
                Let bit_select_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bit_select_ptr, 0, NODE_BIT_SELECT
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bit_select_ptr, 8, id_ptr
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bit_select_ptr, 16, index_expr

                Return bit_select_ptr
            End If
        End If

        Return id_ptr
    End If

    Note: Parenthesized expression
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LPAREN from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let expr be proc parse_expression with parser_ptr

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RPAREN from VerilogLexer

        Return expr
    End If

    Note: Concatenation {expr, expr, ...}
    If token_type is equal to TOKEN_LBRACE from VerilogLexer:
        proc advance with parser_ptr

        Let concat_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with concat_ptr, 0, NODE_CONCATENATION

        Let exprs_list be proc list_create from ListCore

        Let continue be 1

        While continue is equal to 1:
            Set expr to proc parse_expression with parser_ptr
            proc list_append from ListCore with exprs_list, expr

            If proc match with parser_ptr, TOKEN_COMMA from VerilogLexer:
                Note: More expressions
            Otherwise:
                Set continue to 0
            End If
        End While

        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with concat_ptr, 8, exprs_list

        proc expect with parser_ptr, TOKEN_RBRACE from VerilogLexer

        Return concat_ptr
    End If

    Note: Unknown primary expression
    proc add_parse_error with parser_ptr, "Expected primary expression"
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Shared helper to build a NODE_BINARY_OP AST node. Used by every
infix-operator parser (or/and/xor/eq/rel/shift/add/mul/power) so
the AST shape stays uniform - having a single allocator means
later semantic passes need only one schema.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates 32 bytes for a four-field record. Writes node_type =
NODE_BINARY_OP @0, op_type @8, left @16, right @24. Returns the
node pointer. Does NOT touch the parser state - the caller is
responsible for having advanced past the operator token already.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_binary_op" that takes op_type as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bin_op_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 32

    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bin_op_ptr, 0, NODE_BINARY_OP
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bin_op_ptr, 8, op_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bin_op_ptr, 16, left
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with bin_op_ptr, 24, right

    Return bin_op_ptr
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Error Handling
Note: ================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records a parse error at the lexical location of the CURRENT token.
The token's line and column come from the lexer's per-token
metadata so error reports point at the offending byte even after
the parser has skipped ahead in recovery.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Peeks the current token (may be 0 at EOF). Reads line @24 and
column @32 from the token record, defaulting to 0/0 if the token
pointer is null. Allocates a 24-byte error node: message string
@0, line @8, column @16. Reads the parser's errors_list pointer
from @16 and appends the new error node.
@End Implementation
Process called "add_parse_error" that takes parser_ptr as Integer, message as String returns Integer:
    Let token_ptr be proc peek with parser_ptr
    Let line be 0
    Let column be 0

    If token_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Set line to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 24
        Set column to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with token_ptr, 32
    End If

    Let error_ptr be proc allocate from Memory with 24
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with error_ptr, 0, message
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with error_ptr, 8, line
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with error_ptr, 16, column

    Let errors_list be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 16
    proc list_append from ListCore with errors_list, error_ptr

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Public accessor for the parser's accumulated error list. Drivers
call this after parse() returns so they can decide whether to
proceed with semantic analysis or report errors and bail.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the errors_list pointer stored at offset 16 of the
VerilogParser record (the third slot). Returns it directly without
copying.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_errors" that takes parser_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parser_ptr, 16
End Process
